annotationA: RE22677p; delta5-delta2,4-dienoyl-CoA isomerase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: fatty acid beta-oxidation; metabolic process
annotationB: Peroxisomal Multifunctional enzyme type 2 is a multifunctional protein harboring two separate enzyme activities: 2-enoyl-CoA hydratase 2 and 3-hydroxyacyl-CoA dehydrogenase. They function in the peroxisomal fatty acid breakdown spiral of beta-oxidation utilizing the (R)-isomer of the CoA-containing substrate; Belongs to the short-chain dehydrogenases/reductases (SDR) family
